1. Sealed Classes (Standard Feature)
Sealed classes restrict which classes can extend or implement them.

public sealed class Shape permits Circle, Rectangle {}

final class Circle extends Shape {}
final class Rectangle extends Shape {}

Why it matters:
Better control over class hierarchies
Improves maintainability and security
Works well with pattern matching

🔥 Important Rules for Sealed Classes
When a class extends a sealed class, it must be one of these:

1. final
Cannot be extended further.
final class Car extends Vehicle {}

2. sealed
Can again restrict subclasses.
sealed class Car extends Vehicle permits SportsCar {}

3. non-sealed
Removes restriction and allows anyone to extend.
non-sealed class Bike extends Vehicle {}